+- [ ] **Step 5: Implement atomic history publication and latest synchronization**
+
+Use temp sibling files and `os.replace`:
+
+```python
+def _atomic_write_bytes(path: Path, content: bytes) -> None:
+    path.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)
+    temporary = path.with_name(f".{path.name}.{uuid4().hex}.tmp")
+    try:
+        temporary.write_bytes(content)
+        os.replace(temporary, path)
+    finally:
+        if temporary.exists():
+            temporary.unlink()
+```
+
+Publication order:
+
+1. validate workspace and run paths;
+2. write run-history JSON;
+3. calculate canonical JSON SHA;
+4. write run-history Markdown;
+5. only after both history files exist, write latest JSON;
+6. write latest Markdown;
+7. return relative paths.
+
+Run-history paths must not already exist. If either exists, return `blocker_report_history_exists` and do not overwrite it.
+
+When history JSON fails:
+
+- remove stale latest JSON/Markdown best-effort;
+- return no publication paths;
+- add `blocker_report_write_failed`.
+
+When Markdown fails after JSON:
+
+- retain run JSON and its SHA;
+- do not synchronize latest views;
+- remove stale latest views;
+- add `blocker_report_markdown_failed`.
+
+When only latest synchronization fails:
+
+- retain both history paths;
+- set failed latest paths to `None`;
+- add `blocker_report_latest_sync_failed`.
+
