+- [ ] **Step 5: Handle actual run results and auto-open once**
+
+After a `run-tests --run` command result:
+
+```typescript
+if (result.outcome === 'blocked' && result.blockerDetails) {
+  const summary = await verifyExecutionBlockerDetails(
+    workspace,
+    result.blockerDetails,
+  );
+  blockerStore.set(summary);
+  if (
+    summary.reportMarkdown
+    && blockerStore.shouldAutoOpen(workspace, summary.runId)
+  ) {
+    await openReport(summary.reportMarkdown);
+    blockerStore.markAutoOpened(workspace, summary.runId);
+  }
+  refreshWorkflow();
+} else if (isActualRunOutcome(result.outcome)) {
+  blockerStore.clear(workspace);
+  refreshWorkflow();
+}
+```
+
+`isActualRunOutcome` returns true for `passed`, `failed`, `inconclusive`, `timed_out`, and `cancelled`, and false for `planned`.
+
+When a valid blocked envelope has no verified Markdown, keep the summary and show its diagnostics. Do not call `openReport`.
